body:
> if the read fails, we can retake cs_main and check if the block was pruned out from under us. If so, we log and continue, otherwise we can keep crashing on an assert

@maflcko I updated the code to do this. Thus I don't think there is any behavior change.
If the block requested is pruned, we return early before and after this PR. If the block requested is unpruned and we fail to read it, we will crash before and after this PR.

